    "actor_description": "I really thought it would go another way. The hope I'd been holding doesn't shatter-it just folds in on itself, neat and final. My chest feels heavy, like I swallowed a small stone, and my thoughts keep circling the same simple verdict: not this time. I'm not gearing up to fight; I'm letting the loss settle, tasting the dull ache of what could've been. Even my body moves slower, as if it doesn't see the point in hurrying.",
    "description_text": "{actor} seems to sag by a degree, like something inside them unhooked. Their gaze drops and stays there a beat too long; the mouth softens into a thin, tired line. They breathe out-quiet, untheatrical-like they're setting down an expectation they can't carry anymore.",
